{"parentUuid":"6a4b1821-a434-47f3-899d-b1b8ca720adc","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Administrator","sessionId":"11039e2a-cbed-45eb-accf-f84d3fb4cdfe","version":"2.1.49","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"soft-wobbling-shannon","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_011tRE29n7G5XLi8FoA7zuGa","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to use the MCP server to test the RL (rear left) seat heater ECU. They want me to:\n1. Connect via PCAN-USB\n2. Turn on heater at 3-step, 2-step, 1-step and verify detection for each\n\nFrom the CLAUDE.md, the control sequence is:\n1. can_open() - PCAN-USB connection\n2. ign_start() - BCM_02 IGN ON periodic sending\n3. Wait 1 second\n4. uds_request Extended Session\n5. tp_start() - TesterPresent periodic\n6. uds_request heater 3-step ON\n\n\n7. heater_status() to check the response\n8. Then heater OFF\n\nThe key insight is that F016 only supports 3-step ON and OFF commands, and when 3-step is activated, the ECU automatically descends through 3→2→1→OFF, so I'll turn on 3-step once and monitor the automatic descent to verify all three levels are detected.\n\nI need to verify which MCP tools are actually available to me—the user mentioned a pcan MCP server configured in settings, but I'm not seeing those tools in my current list, so I should check whether they're properly loaded or if I need to access them differently. I don't see any pcan-related tools in my available tools, the MCP server might not be connected/running.\n\nLet me check if there are MCP tools available that I'm not seeing. Actually, the tools I have are: Task, TaskOutput, Bash, Glob, Grep, ExitPlanMode, Read, Edit, Write, NotebookEdit, WebFetch, WebSearch, TaskStop, AskUserQuestion, Skill, EnterPlanMode, TaskCreate, TaskGet, TaskUpdate, TaskList.\n\nNo MCP tools. I should try to start the MCP server or use the tools through some other means. Actually, MCP servers in Claude Code are configured